## Feedback to Record

- Adopt a capability-first structure: infrastructure remains top-level, while builder-only forms, modals, and components live in meaningful nested `src/builder/` folders.
- Do not move all builder-specific components into `src/ui/`. Reserve `ui` for domain-neutral atoms, surfaces, and motion primitives.
- Do not make “empty `src/components/`” a success metric. Success means every folder has one clear purpose and ownership boundary.
- Preserve useful nesting. Organize stage views by capability such as `kanban/`, `timeline/`, calendar-oriented views, and `shared/`.
- Avoid oversized “universal” atoms with unrelated optional props. Use a small visual primitive plus semantic wrappers such as status, readiness, and lock badges.
- Do not merge hooks merely to reduce file count; merge only when responsibilities and lifecycle genuinely match.
- Remove the obsolete `DRAFT-PENDING-RESEARCH/` sprint copies before plan activation.
- Replace P3’s unresolved “pick one after reading” choices with explicit implementation decisions.

