## Backend Readiness Corrections

- Keep API DTOs and domain models independent; domain types should not extend transport DTOs.
- Preserve typed mappers as the boundary between mock/API data and domain data.
- Define typed endpoint contracts and mock handlers for every supported endpoint.
- Route services through a transport interface configured to use mocks only.
- Do not implement real fetch, authentication, or backend connectivity in this plan.
- Centralize transport error handling instead of adding repetitive `try/catch` blocks to every service.
- Prove readiness with contract tests, mapper tests, mock persistence tests, and a test showing that transport replacement does not affect consumers.
- Change the success statement from “swap eight service files” to “replace the configured transport while service consumers remain unchanged.”

